<subSubSection id="C34AA094FFC1F13142986C67FD35FD92" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEFF31FFFC1F13142986C67FD35FD92" blockId="8.[151,1436,259,609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis id="B9242F0DFFC1F13142986C67FE9DFE96" bold="true" box="[151,362,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Diagnosis, female</emphasis>
. Body 
<quantity id="4CA85EFAFFC1F13143CE6C67FDDFFE95" box="[449,552,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.44" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" unit="mm" value="2.44">2.44 mm</quantity>
long. Castaneous, metasoma darker. Mandible with two apical teeth, narrow apically. Clypeus very short and slightly concave, apical margin curved upward medially in frontal view. Antenna thick, pedicel long, flagellomeres wider than long, except last. Eye with sparse short setae. Frons weakly coriaceous, nearly polished, punctures sparse and inconspicuous. LH 1.15 WH, WF 0.52 WH, WF 1.47 HE. Vertex barely outcurved. Sides of head subparallel. VOL 1.28 HE. Mesoscutum 1.1 as wide as long. Metapectal-propodeal disc nearly quadrate, side subparallel, base only slightly constricted, without median and posterior carinae. Micropterous, wings much shorter than tegula. Profemur 1.6 as long as wide. Metasoma stout, 0.56 as long as body, apical margin of sternites IV–VI conspicuously bi-emarginated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
